This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new flow-based model for density estimation. The paper also focuses on improving the density modeling performance of flow-based models, which is a common research topic in the machine learning community. 

Additionally, the paper deals with image benchmarks, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper also proposes new design choices for flow-based models, which may fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The use of variational dequantization and architecture design in the proposed model may also suggest that the paper belongs to the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), respectively.
